        <!-- OpenAI API Models with current pricing (March 2026)
             Sources: https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/pricing
                      https://openai.com/api/pricing/

             Energy benchmarks (kWh per 1K tokens) estimated from:
             Luccioni et al. "Power Hungry Processing" (ACM FAccT 2024)
             IEA "Energy and AI" report (April 2025)
             Epoch AI inference compute estimates (2025)
             Patterson et al. "Carbon Emissions and Large Neural Networks" (2021)

             Methodology: energy_kwh_per_1k_tokens scales with model parameter
             count and architecture complexity. Flagship ~0.0002 kWh/1K,
             mini ~0.00004 kWh/1K, nano ~0.00002 kWh/1K.
             Reasoning models have ~2x overhead due to chain of thought compute.
        -->

